  "description": "<i>Roberta Williams' King's Quest I: Quest for the Crown</i> is a remake of <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/game/kings-quest\">King's Quest</a>. It uses Sierra's 16-color SCI game interpreter, making it visually similar to the series' <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/game/kings-quest-iv-the-perils-of-rosella\">fourth</a> installment, with more detailed EGA full-screen graphics and optional mouse support, while retaining text-based input and interaction. This version also has a musical score that supports sound cards, as opposed to the speaker-only output of the original release.<br><br>Several changes have been made to the game's locations and script. A few new characters appear in the remake, and some of the conversations feature additional lines. A number of puzzles have slightly different solutions, and some objects are found in different places than they were in the original version.",
